Drug Platform Technology: Monospecific IgG1 ADC, genetically conjugated via stochastic or site-specific linker technology
Mechanism of Action: ntibody binds c‑Met, internalized, releases topoisomerase I inhibitor for cytotoxicity, with possible bystander effects
Linker: Cleavable (designed to release payload intracellularly; typical for Top1i ADCs)
Trial Design: Open-label, dose-escalation followed by expansion cohorts; later includes randomized Phase 2/3 studies
Number of Arms: Multiple dose cohorts; expansion monotherapy and combination arms; upcoming randomized arms (e.g., vs Lonsurf+Bev)
Comparator Arm: None in initial, later arms include active comparators (e.g., Lonsurf + bevacizumab)
Combo Therapy Status: Monotherapy in Phase 1; planned combos with bevacizumab, budigalimab, osimertinib, fluoropyrimidines
Line of Therapy: Heavily pretreated/refractory solid tumors; new arms in earlier lines planned
Biomarker Strategy: MET protein expression by IHC (≥10% 3+ for CRC expansion); MET amplification also analyzed (ctDNA
Diagnostic Assay: MET IHC; ctDNA panels (GuardantINFINITY) in exploratory studies
Regulatory Designations: No public Breakthrough, ODD, or Fast Track yet
Efficacy: ORR: NSCLC EGFR-WT: ~48% (2.4–3 mg/kg), CBR ~85% at median 6.8 mo follow-up; CRC MET‑high by IHC: 37.5%; MET-low: 14%; Overall across solid tumors: ORR ~63%, median PFS ~9 mo
Durability: Median PFS ~9 months; DOR immature but ongoing responders at data cutoff
Safety: Common AEs: Hematologic (anemia, neutropenia, thrombocytopenia), fatigue, nausea; ILD/pneumonitis rare class effect; Grade 3‑4: Hematologic ~35%; GI ~4%; Fatal TEAEs: ~17% (mostly disease progression; some infection, respiratory distress, pneumonitis)

chembl_target: Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 17

Phase: Phase I expansion in PDAC, GEA, etc.

DO: varian, endometrial, breast, NSCLC, and mesothelioma patients
